{"title_page": "Practical Joke (horse)", "text_new": "{{Short description|American-bred Thoroughbred racehorse}}\n\n{{Infobox racehorse\n| horsename = Practical Joke\n| image_name = PracticalJoke-BCJuv2016-2.jpg\n| caption = Practical Joke at the 2016 Breeders' Cup Juvenile\n| sire = [[Into Mischief]]\n| grandsire = [[Harlan's Holiday]]\n| dam = Halo Humor\n| damsire = [[Distorted Humor]]\n| sex = [[Colt (horse)|Colt]]\n| foaled = April 15, 2014\n| country = United States\n| color = [[Bay (horse)|Bay]]\n| breeder = Whispering Oaks\n| owner = [[Klaravich Stables]] and William Lawrence\n| trainer = [[Chad C. Brown]]\n| record = 12: 5\u20132\u20133\n| earnings =  $1,795,800<ref name=\"EquibaseProfile\">{{cite web|title=Practical Joke Profile|url=http://www.equibase.com/profiles/Results.cfm?type=Horse&refno=9692577&registry=T&rbt=TB|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=5 December 2017}}</ref>\n| race = [[Hopeful Stakes]] (2016)<br>[[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]] (2016)<br>[[Dwyer Stakes]] (2017)<br>[[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]] (2017)\n| awards=\n| honours = \n| updated= \n}}\n\n'''Practical Joke''' (foaled April 15, 2014 in Kentucky) is a retired multiple Grade I-winning American [[Thoroughbred]] [[racehorse]] whose wins included the [[Hopeful Stakes|Hopeful]], [[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne]] and [[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]].\n\n==Background==\nPractical Joke is a bay colt with a star and no other white markings who was bred in Kentucky by Whispering Oaks. He is from the fifth crop of foals by [[Into Mischief]], a stakes winning son of [[Harlan's Holiday]] and out of Leslie's Lady, who later produced champion [[Beholder (horse)|Beholder]]. Into Mischief originally stood for only $12,500, but his profile increased when he sired two-time Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile winner [[Goldencents]]. Practical Joke is the fourth foal out of the stakes placed mare Halo Humor, by [[Distorted Humor]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sparkman|first1=John P.|title=Practical Joke is Into Mischief's latest serious runner|url=http://www.drf.com/news/sparkman-practical-joke-mischiefs-latest-serious-runner|website=Daily Racing Form|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref> He was sold twice as a yearling in 2015, first in the [[Keeneland Sales|Keeneland]] January mixed sale for $135,000 and then at the Keeneland September sale for $240,000.<ref name=EquibaseProfile />\n\n==Racing career==\n===2016: two-year-old season===\nPractical Joke started his career in a 6 furlong [[Maiden race|Maiden Special Weight]] at [[Saratoga Race Course|Saratoga]] on August 6. He was sent off as the 5\u201312 favorite ridden by [[Irad Ortiz Jr.]]. Leaving the gate, he bumped with another horse and was near the back of the pack down the backstretch. He went wide on the turn and started to close quickly on the early leaders, then drew away in the stretch to win by 5 lengths.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chart for Saratoga - August 6, 2016|url=http://www.equibase.com/premium/chartEmb.cfm?track=SAR&raceDate=08/06/2016&cy=USA&rn=2|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe then entered the [[Hopeful Stakes]] on September 9 where he was the 2-1 second choice in a field of six behind [[Classic Empire]]. Ridden by [[Jose Ortiz (jockey)|Jose Ortiz]], he settled at the back of the pack behind a slow early pace, then swung wide around the turn. In the stretch, he battled with Royal Copy and Pretty Boy Flash but inched away late in the final furlong to win by a neck. Ortiz said after the race, \"He was running the whole way. He gave me a great turn of foot when I got him in the clear but the other two horses were in front and they kept fighting a little bit. As soon as he put a head in front, he kept going.\"<ref name=\"Hopeful\">{{cite web|last1=Hammonds|first1=Evan|title=Practical Joke Takes the Hopeful|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/214793/practical-joke-takes-the-hopeful|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe win was particularly satisfying for trainer Chad Brown, a trainer with a good reputation with fillies and [[turf]] horses, but who had never won a Grade I race with a colt on the dirt. \"It's really a dream come true\", said Brown. \"I'm just so happy. What a great moment for me and my staff... It's been a pleasure to train him. That first race I thought he ran well and his second time here he also came back to run a huge race.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Singelais|first1=Mark|title=Chad Brown ends \"dream\" meet with Hopeful win|url=http://www.timesunion.com/sports/article/Chad-Brown-ends-dream-meet-with-Hopeful-win-9204381.php|website=Times Union|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke's final prep for the Breeders' Cup Juvenile was the [[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]] at [[Belmont Racetrack|Belmont Park]] on October 8. He was the 5-2 second choice behind Syndergaard at 9-5. Now ridden by [[Joel Rosario]], he broke awkwardly and ducked in toward the rail, then settled into mid-pack. He made his move around the turn and in the stretch he got even with Syndergaard and dueled down to the wire to win a head bobbing finish by a nose in a time of 1:34.68. It was the fourth fastest [[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]] in the history of the race.<ref>http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/215689/practical-joke-edges-syndergaard-in-champagne</ref> Rosario stated after the race, \"He kind of broke awkward on the inside and I had to use him a little through the chute. He was looking around and it took him a little time to get back in the race but he was fine after that. They were going really fast up front but it looks like the more distance he gets to run into the better he gets. For a second when I got to the other horse (Syndergaard) he waited a little bit. He's still a young horse if anything but looks good going forward.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Angst|first1=Frank|title=Practical Joke Edges Syndergaard in Champagne|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/215689/practical-joke-edges-syndergaard-in-champagne|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Breeders' Cup Juvenile]] was held at Santa Anita race track on November 5. Practical Joke was one of several horses at 7-1 odds in a highly competitive field of thirteen that included Grade I winners [[Klimt (horse)|Klimt]] (Del Mar Futurity), [[Gormley (horse)|Gormley]] (FrontRunner) and [[Classic Empire]] (Breeders' Futurity). At the break, Practical Joke bumped with Not This Time, then settled into mid pack. On the far turn, he angled to the outside and pulled into third place but finished over seven lengths behind Classic Empire and Not This Time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chart of the 2016 Breeders' Cup Juvenile|url=http://www.equibase.com/premium/chartEmb.cfm?track=SA&raceDate=11/05/2016&cy=USA&rn=8|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017: three-year-old season===\nPractical Joke began the year as one of the top-ranked colts for the [[2017 Kentucky Derby]], although concerns were expressed about the lack of stamina influences in his pedigree.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Haskin|first1=Steve|title=Derby Dozen - January 24, 2017|url=http://cs.bloodhorse.com/blogs/kentucky-derby-dozen/archive/2017/01/24/derby-dozen-january-24-2017-presented-by-shadwell-farm.aspx|website=cs.bloodhorse.com|accessdate=17 April 2017|language=en}}</ref> He made his first start of 2017 in the [[Fountain of Youth Stakes]] on March 4 at Gulfstream Park. After settling in the middle of the pack during the early running, Practical Joke moved to the lead around the far turn but was passed in the stretch by Gunnevera. Brown was happy with the performance, believing Practical Joke needed the race.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wincze Hughes|first1=Alicia|title=Gunnevera Comes From Clouds in Fountain of Youth|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/220245/gunnevera-comes-from-clouds-in-fountain-of-youth|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=17 April 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke made his next start in the [[Blue Grass Stakes]] on April 8 at [[Keeneland]] racetrack. He made a sustained drive down the stretch and finished just three-quarters of a length behind longshot Irap, with highly regarded McCraken three lengths behind in third. Despite concerns over Practical Joke's stamina, Brown was cautiously optimistic about the colt's prospects in the Derby. \"Maybe this is a year that we want to take a shot because we have a horse that has the points [earned in the [[2017 Road to the Kentucky Derby]]], and he did sustain his run.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Blue Grass Hero Irap in Good Order After Shocking Win|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/220899/blue-grass-hero-irap-in-good-order-after-shocking-win|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=17 April 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Kentucky Derby]] was held on May 6 over a wet-fast track at [[Churchill Downs]]. Practical Joke drew post position 19 but Rosario was able to guide him over to the rail to save ground around the first turn. In the final turn, Practical Joke moved to the outside and made a strong run to advance to fourth in mid-stretch before tiring slightly and finishing fifth. Brown was pleased by the effort, saying, \"He got a great trip from that post...He's a very fine racehorse. He just can't go that far. But he was fighting and trying.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wincze Hughes|first1=Alicia|title=Always Dreaming in Good Order After Derby Triumph|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/221471/always-dreaming-in-good-order-after-derby-triumph|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 July 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chart for the 2017 Kentucky Derby|url=http://www.equibase.com/premium/chartEmb.cfm?track=CD&raceDate=05/06/2017&cy=USA&rn=12|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=10 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n[[File:MonmouthPark-Haskell2017-PracticalJoke.jpg|thumb|left|Practical Joke in the walking ring before the 2017 Haskell Invitational at Monmouth Park]]\nBrown gave the colt a layoff then entered him in the [[Dwyer Stakes]] at Belmont Park on July 8 where he was made the 4-5 favorite. Practical Joke rated in fourth behind the early pacemakers, but was trapped on the inside as they entered the stretch. Swung wide by Rosario, he finally found racing room and quickly pulled away to win by two lengths. Brown was pleased. \"He really ran well today. I certainly think it's the best race he's ever won.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hammond|first1=Evan|title=Practical Joke Shines in Dwyer|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/222468/practical-joke-shines-in-dwyer|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=6 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn July 30, Practical Joke made his next start in the [[Haskell Invitational]] at Monmouth Park where he faced a high quality field that included old rival McCraken, Belmont Stakes runner-up [[Irish War Cry]] and Santa Anita Derby winner [[Girvin]]. After being bumped at the start, Practical Joke rated in the middle of the pack trailed by McCraken and Girvin. Turning into the stretch, McCraken made his move and opened a one-length lead while Practical Joke and Girvin started closing ground on the outside. In a photo finish, Girvin prevailed over McCraken by a nose with Practical Joke just half a length behind in third.<ref>{{cite web|title=Girvin Gets it Done in Haskell Invitational|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/222824/girvin-gets-it-done-in-haskell-invitational|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=6 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn August 26, Practical Joke started in the [[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]] at [[Saratoga Race Course]]. He drew post 1 and again was ridden by Rosario. He broke well and settled towards the rear of the field, as Takaful set the pace. Rosario started asking Practical Joke to go around the final turn, and Practical Joke unleashed a sustained rally, winning by 1 1/4 lengths with a time of 1:21.96 for seven furlongs. With the win, Practical Joke earned the third grade one victory of his career. Brown stated after the race: \"To cut back all the way to seven-eighths after a tough race in the Haskell, I'm so proud of this horse. It was his third race in seven weeks. He's our iron horse.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Practical Joke Too Good in H. Allen Jerkens|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/223287/practical-joke-too-good-in-h-allen-jerkens|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke made his next start in the [[Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile]] at Del Mar on November 3. Unfortunately he drew the outside post position, a major disadvantage in a two-turn mile. He broke slowly and was angled sharply over to the rail to save ground on the first turn. Down the backstretch, he raced near the back of the field, then started to make up position around the second turn. With a quarter of a mile remaining, he was swung wide and closed down the stretch, finishing fourth.<ref>{{cite web|title=Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile: Two turns the issue for Practical Joke {{!}} Daily Racing Form|url=http://www.drf.com/news/breeders-cup-dirt-mile-two-turns-issue-practical-joke|website=www.drf.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"BCDM\">{{cite web|title=Chart of the Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile|url=http://www.equibase.com/static/chart/pdf/DMR110317USA7.pdf|website=Equibase|accessdate=10 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke's final start was in the [[Cigar Mile Handicap|Cigar Mile]] on December 2 at Aqueduct. He settled at the back of the pack, over 12 lengths behind a fast early pace. Around the far turn, he moved wide and circled the field to make up ground but was still finished well back in third  behind Sharp Azteca and Mind Your Biscuits. \"It was hard to make up ground today on this track,\" commented Brown. \"That said, the winner was very impressive, and I don't think it would have mattered how the track was playing; it looked like nobody was going to beat him today.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Sharp Azteca Rolls to Cigar Mile Score|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/225010/sharp-azteca-rolls-to-cigar-mile-score|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=7 March 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Race record==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:80%;\"\n|-\n! Date\n!  Track\n!  Race\n! Grade\n! Distance\n! Finish\n! Odds\n! Margin\n!  Time\n|-\n|8/6/2016\n|[[Saratoga Race Course|Saratoga]]\n|Maiden Special Weight\n|Maiden\n|6 [[furlong]]s\n|1\n|2.40*\n|5 lengths\n|1:10.02\n|-\n|9/5/2016\n|[[Saratoga Race Course|Saratoga]]\n|[[Hopeful Stakes]]\n|I\n|7 furlongs\n|1\n|2.10\n|Neck\n|1:23.39\n|-\n|10/8/2016\n|[[Belmont Park|Belmont]]\n|[[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]]\n|I\n|8 furlongs\n|1\n|2.95\n|Nose\n|1:34.68\n|-\n|11/5/2016\n|[[Santa Anita race track|Santa Anita]]\n|[[Breeders' Cup Juvenile]]\n|I\n|{{frac|1|1|16}} miles\n|3\n|7.80\n|({{frac|7|1|2}} lengths)\n|1:42.60\n|-\n|3/4/2017\n|[[Gulfstream Park]]\n|[[Fountain of Youth Stakes]]\n|II\n|{{frac|1|1|16}} miles\n|2\n|3.40\n|({{frac|5|3|4}} lengths)\n|1:44.25\n|-\n|4/8/2017\n|[[Keeneland]]\n|[[Blue Grass Stakes]]\n|II\n|{{frac|1|1|8}} miles\n|2\n|3.60\n|({{frac|3|4}} lengths)\n|1:50.39\n|-\n|5/6/2017\n|[[Churchill Downs]]\n|[[Kentucky Derby]]\n|I\n|{{frac|1|1|4}} miles\n|5\n|27.80\n|({{frac|9|1|2}} lengths)\n|2:03.59\n|-\n|7/9/2017\n|[[Belmont Park]]\n|[[Dwyer Stakes]]\n|III\n|1 mile\n|1\n|0.75*\n|2 lengths\n|1:35.16\n|-\n|7/30/2017\n|[[Monmouth Park]]\n|[[Haskell Invitational]]\n|I\n|{{frac|1|1|8}} miles\n|3\n|4.40\n|({{frac|1|2}} length\n|1:48.35\n|-\n|8/26/2017\n|[[Saratoga Race Course]]\n|[[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]]\n|I\n|7 Furlongs\n|1\n|2.00*\n|1 1/4 lengths\n|1:21.96\n|-\n|11/3/2017\n|[[Del Mar racetrack|Del Mar]]\n|[[Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile]]\n|I\n|1 mile\n|4\n|5.80\n|5 1/4 lengths\n|1:35.20\n|-\n|12/2/2017\n|Aqueduct\n|Cigar Mile\n|I\n|1 mile\n|3\n|2.85\n|8 lengths\n|1:35.17\n|}\n\nSource: Equibase Charts<ref name=EquibaseProfile />\n\n==Retirement==\nAfter his win in the Allen Jerkens, it was announced that his breeding rights were purchased by [[Ashford Stud]] (a division of the international operation [[Coolmore Stud]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=Practical Joke to Ashford Stud for 2018|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/223424/practical-joke-to-ashford-stud-for-2018|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref> He was retired after the Cigar Mile and his stud fee for 2018 was set at $30,000.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ashford Stud Sets Fees for Practical Joke, Cupid|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/224636/ashford-stud-sets-fees-for-practical-joke-cupid|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Pedigree==\n{{Pedigree\n|name = Practical Joke, bay colt, 2014\n|f = Into Mischief <br /> 2005\n|m = Halo Humor <br /> 2003\n|ff = [[Harlan's Holiday]] <br /> 1999\n|fm = Leslie's Lady <br /> 1996\n|mf = [[Distorted Humor]] <br /> 1993\n|mm = Gilded Halo <br /> 1996\n|fff = Harlan\n|ffm = Christmas In Aiken\n|fmf = Tricky Creek\n|fmm = Crystal Lady\n|mff = [[Forty Niner (horse)|Forty Niner]]\n|mfm = Danzig's Beauty\n|mmf = [[Gilded Time]]\n|mmm = Careless Halo\n|ffff = [[Storm Cat]]\n|fffm = Country Romance\n|ffmf = [[Affirmed]]\n|ffmm = Dowager\n|fmff = Clever Trick\n|fmfm = Battle Creek Girl\n|fmmf = [[Stop The Music (horse)|Stop the Music]]\n|fmmm = One Last Bird\n|mfff = [[Mr. Prospector]]\n|mffm = File\n|mfmf = [[Danzig (horse)|Danzig]]\n|mfmm = Sweetest Chant\n|mmff = Timeless Moment\n|mmfm = Gilded Lilly\n|mmmf = [[Sunny's Halo]]\n|mmmm = Careless Moment (family: A4<ref>{{cite web|title=Practical Joke Horse Pedigree|url=http://www.pedigreequery.com/practical+joke3|website=www.pedigreequery.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>)\n}}\n\nPractical Joke is inbred 5 x 5 to Halo, meaning Halo appears twice in the fifth generation of Practical Joke's pedigree.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2014 racehorse births]]\n[[Category:Thoroughbred family A4]]\n[[Category:Racehorses bred in Kentucky]]\n[[Category:Racehorses trained in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American-bred Thoroughbred racehorse}}\n\n{{Infobox racehorse\n| horsename = Practical Joke\n| image_name = PracticalJoke-BCJuv2016-2.jpg\n| caption = Practical Joke at the 2016 Breeders' Cup Juvenile\n| sire = [[Into Mischief]]\n| grandsire = [[Harlan's Holiday]]\n| dam = Halo Humor\n| damsire = [[Distorted Humor]]\n| sex = [[Colt (horse)|Colt]]\n| foaled = April 15, 2014\n| country = United States\n| color = [[Bay (horse)|Bay]]\n| breeder = Whispering Oaks\n| owner = [[Klaravich Stables]] and William Lawrence\n| trainer = [[Chad C. Brown]]\n| record = 12: 5\u20132\u20133\n| earnings =  $1,795,800<ref name=\"EquibaseProfile\">{{cite web|title=Practical Joke Profile|url=http://www.equibase.com/profiles/Results.cfm?type=Horse&refno=9692577&registry=T&rbt=TB|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=5 December 2017}}</ref>\n| race = [[Hopeful Stakes]] (2016)<br>[[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]] (2016)<br>[[Dwyer Stakes]] (2017)<br>[[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]] (2017)\n| awards=\n| honours = \n| updated= \n}}\n\n'''Practical Joke''' (foaled April 15, 2014 in Kentucky) is a retired multiple Grade I-winning American [[Thoroughbred]] [[racehorse]] whose wins included the [[Hopeful Stakes|Hopeful]], [[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne]] and [[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]].\n\n==Background==\nPractical Joke is a bay colt with a star and no other white markings who was bred in Kentucky by Whispering Oaks. He is from the fifth crop of foals by [[Into Mischief]], by [[Harlan's Holiday]] and out of Leslie's Lady, who later produced champion [[Beholder (horse)|Beholder]]. Into Mischief originally stood for only $12,500, but his profile increased when he sired two-time Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile winner [[Goldencents]]. Practical Joke is the fourth foal out of the stakes placed mare Halo Humor, by [[Distorted Humor]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sparkman|first1=John P.|title=Practical Joke is Into Mischief's latest serious runner|url=http://www.drf.com/news/sparkman-practical-joke-mischiefs-latest-serious-runner|website=Daily Racing Form|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref> He was sold twice as a yearling in 2015, first in the [[Keeneland Sales|Keeneland]] January mixed sale for $135,000 and then at the Keeneland September sale for $240,000.<ref name=EquibaseProfile />\n\n==Racing career==\n===2016: two-year-old season===\nPractical Joke started his career in a 6 furlong [[Maiden race|Maiden Special Weight]] at [[Saratoga Race Course|Saratoga]] on August 6. He was sent off as the 5\u201312 favorite ridden by [[Irad Ortiz Jr.]]. Leaving the gate, he bumped with another horse and was near the back of the pack down the backstretch. He went wide on the turn and started to close quickly on the early leaders, then drew away in the stretch to win by 5 lengths.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chart for Saratoga - August 6, 2016|url=http://www.equibase.com/premium/chartEmb.cfm?track=SAR&raceDate=08/06/2016&cy=USA&rn=2|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nHe then entered the [[Hopeful Stakes]] on September 9 where he was the 2-1 second choice in a field of six behind [[Classic Empire]]. Ridden by [[Jose Ortiz (jockey)|Jose Ortiz]], he settled at the back of the pack behind a slow early pace, then swung wide around the turn. In the stretch, he battled with Royal Copy and Pretty Boy Flash but inched away late in the final furlong to win by a neck. Ortiz said after the race, \"He was running the whole way. He gave me a great turn of foot when I got him in the clear but the other two horses were in front and they kept fighting a little bit. As soon as he put a head in front, he kept going.\"<ref name=\"Hopeful\">{{cite web|last1=Hammonds|first1=Evan|title=Practical Joke Takes the Hopeful|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/214793/practical-joke-takes-the-hopeful|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe win was particularly satisfying for trainer Chad Brown, a trainer with a good reputation with fillies and [[turf]] horses, but who had never won a Grade I race with a colt on the dirt. \"It's really a dream come true\", said Brown. \"I'm just so happy. What a great moment for me and my staff... It's been a pleasure to train him. That first race I thought he ran well and his second time here he also came back to run a huge race.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Singelais|first1=Mark|title=Chad Brown ends \"dream\" meet with Hopeful win|url=http://www.timesunion.com/sports/article/Chad-Brown-ends-dream-meet-with-Hopeful-win-9204381.php|website=Times Union|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke's final prep for the Breeders' Cup Juvenile was the [[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]] at [[Belmont Racetrack|Belmont Park]] on October 8. He was the 5-2 second choice behind Syndergaard at 9-5. Now ridden by [[Joel Rosario]], he broke awkwardly and ducked in toward the rail, then settled into mid-pack. He made his move around the turn and in the stretch he got even with Syndergaard and dueled down to the wire to win a head bobbing finish by a nose in a time of 1:34.68. It was the fourth fastest [[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]] in the history of the race.<ref>http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/215689/practical-joke-edges-syndergaard-in-champagne</ref> Rosario stated after the race, \"He kind of broke awkward on the inside and I had to use him a little through the chute. He was looking around and it took him a little time to get back in the race but he was fine after that. They were going really fast up front but it looks like the more distance he gets to run into the better he gets. For a second when I got to the other horse (Syndergaard) he waited a little bit. He's still a young horse if anything but looks good going forward.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Angst|first1=Frank|title=Practical Joke Edges Syndergaard in Champagne|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/215689/practical-joke-edges-syndergaard-in-champagne|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Breeders' Cup Juvenile]] was held at Santa Anita race track on November 5. Practical Joke was one of several horses at 7-1 odds in a highly competitive field of thirteen that included Grade I winners [[Klimt (horse)|Klimt]] (Del Mar Futurity), [[Gormley (horse)|Gormley]] (FrontRunner) and [[Classic Empire]] (Breeders' Futurity). At the break, Practical Joke bumped with Not This Time, then settled into mid pack. On the far turn, he angled to the outside and pulled into third place but finished over seven lengths behind Classic Empire and Not This Time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chart of the 2016 Breeders' Cup Juvenile|url=http://www.equibase.com/premium/chartEmb.cfm?track=SA&raceDate=11/05/2016&cy=USA&rn=8|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017: three-year-old season===\nPractical Joke began the year as one of the top-ranked colts for the [[2017 Kentucky Derby]], although concerns were expressed about the lack of stamina influences in his pedigree.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Haskin|first1=Steve|title=Derby Dozen - January 24, 2017|url=http://cs.bloodhorse.com/blogs/kentucky-derby-dozen/archive/2017/01/24/derby-dozen-january-24-2017-presented-by-shadwell-farm.aspx|website=cs.bloodhorse.com|accessdate=17 April 2017|language=en}}</ref> He made his first start of 2017 in the [[Fountain of Youth Stakes]] on March 4 at Gulfstream Park. After settling in the middle of the pack during the early running, Practical Joke moved to the lead around the far turn but was passed in the stretch by Gunnevera. Brown was happy with the performance, believing Practical Joke needed the race.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wincze Hughes|first1=Alicia|title=Gunnevera Comes From Clouds in Fountain of Youth|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/220245/gunnevera-comes-from-clouds-in-fountain-of-youth|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=17 April 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke made his next start in the [[Blue Grass Stakes]] on April 8 at [[Keeneland]] racetrack. He made a sustained drive down the stretch and finished just three-quarters of a length behind longshot Irap, with highly regarded McCraken three lengths behind in third. Despite concerns over Practical Joke's stamina, Brown was cautiously optimistic about the colt's prospects in the Derby. \"Maybe this is a year that we want to take a shot because we have a horse that has the points [earned in the [[2017 Road to the Kentucky Derby]]], and he did sustain his run.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Blue Grass Hero Irap in Good Order After Shocking Win|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/220899/blue-grass-hero-irap-in-good-order-after-shocking-win|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=17 April 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Kentucky Derby]] was held on May 6 over a wet-fast track at [[Churchill Downs]]. Practical Joke drew post position 19 but Rosario was able to guide him over to the rail to save ground around the first turn. In the final turn, Practical Joke moved to the outside and made a strong run to advance to fourth in mid-stretch before tiring slightly and finishing fifth. Brown was pleased by the effort, saying, \"He got a great trip from that post...He's a very fine racehorse. He just can't go that far. But he was fighting and trying.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wincze Hughes|first1=Alicia|title=Always Dreaming in Good Order After Derby Triumph|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/221471/always-dreaming-in-good-order-after-derby-triumph|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 July 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chart for the 2017 Kentucky Derby|url=http://www.equibase.com/premium/chartEmb.cfm?track=CD&raceDate=05/06/2017&cy=USA&rn=12|website=www.equibase.com|accessdate=10 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n[[File:MonmouthPark-Haskell2017-PracticalJoke.jpg|thumb|left|Practical Joke in the walking ring before the 2017 Haskell Invitational at Monmouth Park]]\nBrown gave the colt a layoff then entered him in the [[Dwyer Stakes]] at Belmont Park on July 8 where he was made the 4-5 favorite. Practical Joke rated in fourth behind the early pacemakers, but was trapped on the inside as they entered the stretch. Swung wide by Rosario, he finally found racing room and quickly pulled away to win by two lengths. Brown was pleased. \"He really ran well today. I certainly think it's the best race he's ever won.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hammond|first1=Evan|title=Practical Joke Shines in Dwyer|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/222468/practical-joke-shines-in-dwyer|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=6 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn July 30, Practical Joke made his next start in the [[Haskell Invitational]] at Monmouth Park where he faced a high quality field that included old rival McCraken, Belmont Stakes runner-up [[Irish War Cry]] and Santa Anita Derby winner [[Girvin]]. After being bumped at the start, Practical Joke rated in the middle of the pack trailed by McCraken and Girvin. Turning into the stretch, McCraken made his move and opened a one-length lead while Practical Joke and Girvin started closing ground on the outside. In a photo finish, Girvin prevailed over McCraken by a nose with Practical Joke just half a length behind in third.<ref>{{cite web|title=Girvin Gets it Done in Haskell Invitational|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/222824/girvin-gets-it-done-in-haskell-invitational|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=6 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn August 26, Practical Joke started in the [[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]] at [[Saratoga Race Course]]. He drew post 1 and again was ridden by Rosario. He broke well and settled towards the rear of the field, as Takaful set the pace. Rosario started asking Practical Joke to go around the final turn, and Practical Joke unleashed a sustained rally, winning by 1 1/4 lengths with a time of 1:21.96 for seven furlongs. With the win, Practical Joke earned the third grade one victory of his career. Brown stated after the race: \"To cut back all the way to seven-eighths after a tough race in the Haskell, I'm so proud of this horse. It was his third race in seven weeks. He's our iron horse.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Practical Joke Too Good in H. Allen Jerkens|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/223287/practical-joke-too-good-in-h-allen-jerkens|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke made his next start in the [[Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile]] at Del Mar on November 3. Unfortunately he drew the outside post position, a major disadvantage in a two-turn mile. He broke slowly and was angled sharply over to the rail to save ground on the first turn. Down the backstretch, he raced near the back of the field, then started to make up position around the second turn. With a quarter of a mile remaining, he was swung wide and closed down the stretch, finishing fourth.<ref>{{cite web|title=Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile: Two turns the issue for Practical Joke {{!}} Daily Racing Form|url=http://www.drf.com/news/breeders-cup-dirt-mile-two-turns-issue-practical-joke|website=www.drf.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"BCDM\">{{cite web|title=Chart of the Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile|url=http://www.equibase.com/static/chart/pdf/DMR110317USA7.pdf|website=Equibase|accessdate=10 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nPractical Joke's final start was in the [[Cigar Mile Handicap|Cigar Mile]] on December 2 at Aqueduct. He settled at the back of the pack, over 12 lengths behind a fast early pace. Around the far turn, he moved wide and circled the field to make up ground but was still finished well back in third  behind Sharp Azteca and Mind Your Biscuits. \"It was hard to make up ground today on this track,\" commented Brown. \"That said, the winner was very impressive, and I don't think it would have mattered how the track was playing; it looked like nobody was going to beat him today.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Sharp Azteca Rolls to Cigar Mile Score|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/225010/sharp-azteca-rolls-to-cigar-mile-score|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=7 March 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Race record==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:80%;\"\n|-\n! Date\n!  Track\n!  Race\n! Grade\n! Distance\n! Finish\n! Odds\n! Margin\n!  Time\n|-\n|8/6/2016\n|[[Saratoga Race Course|Saratoga]]\n|Maiden Special Weight\n|Maiden\n|6 [[furlong]]s\n|1\n|2.40*\n|5 lengths\n|1:10.02\n|-\n|9/5/2016\n|[[Saratoga Race Course|Saratoga]]\n|[[Hopeful Stakes]]\n|I\n|7 furlongs\n|1\n|2.10\n|Neck\n|1:23.39\n|-\n|10/8/2016\n|[[Belmont Park|Belmont]]\n|[[Champagne Stakes (United States)|Champagne Stakes]]\n|I\n|8 furlongs\n|1\n|2.95\n|Nose\n|1:34.68\n|-\n|11/5/2016\n|[[Santa Anita race track|Santa Anita]]\n|[[Breeders' Cup Juvenile]]\n|I\n|{{frac|1|1|16}} miles\n|3\n|7.80\n|({{frac|7|1|2}} lengths)\n|1:42.60\n|-\n|3/4/2017\n|[[Gulfstream Park]]\n|[[Fountain of Youth Stakes]]\n|II\n|{{frac|1|1|16}} miles\n|2\n|3.40\n|({{frac|5|3|4}} lengths)\n|1:44.25\n|-\n|4/8/2017\n|[[Keeneland]]\n|[[Blue Grass Stakes]]\n|II\n|{{frac|1|1|8}} miles\n|2\n|3.60\n|({{frac|3|4}} lengths)\n|1:50.39\n|-\n|5/6/2017\n|[[Churchill Downs]]\n|[[Kentucky Derby]]\n|I\n|{{frac|1|1|4}} miles\n|5\n|27.80\n|({{frac|9|1|2}} lengths)\n|2:03.59\n|-\n|7/9/2017\n|[[Belmont Park]]\n|[[Dwyer Stakes]]\n|III\n|1 mile\n|1\n|0.75*\n|2 lengths\n|1:35.16\n|-\n|7/30/2017\n|[[Monmouth Park]]\n|[[Haskell Invitational]]\n|I\n|{{frac|1|1|8}} miles\n|3\n|4.40\n|({{frac|1|2}} length\n|1:48.35\n|-\n|8/26/2017\n|[[Saratoga Race Course]]\n|[[H. Allen Jerkens Memorial Stakes]]\n|I\n|7 Furlongs\n|1\n|2.00*\n|1 1/4 lengths\n|1:21.96\n|-\n|11/3/2017\n|[[Del Mar racetrack|Del Mar]]\n|[[Breeders' Cup Dirt Mile]]\n|I\n|1 mile\n|4\n|5.80\n|5 1/4 lengths\n|1:35.20\n|-\n|12/2/2017\n|Aqueduct\n|Cigar Mile\n|I\n|1 mile\n|3\n|2.85\n|8 lengths\n|1:35.17\n|}\n\nSource: Equibase Charts<ref name=EquibaseProfile />\n\n==Retirement==\nAfter his win in the Allen Jerkens, it was announced that his breeding rights were purchased by [[Ashford Stud]] (a division of the international operation [[Coolmore Stud]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=Practical Joke to Ashford Stud for 2018|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/223424/practical-joke-to-ashford-stud-for-2018|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref> He was retired after the Cigar Mile and his stud fee for 2018 was set at $30,000.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ashford Stud Sets Fees for Practical Joke, Cupid|url=https://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/224636/ashford-stud-sets-fees-for-practical-joke-cupid|website=BloodHorse.com|accessdate=10 November 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Pedigree==\n{{Pedigree\n|name = Practical Joke, bay colt, 2014\n|f = Into Mischief <br /> 2005\n|m = Halo Humor <br /> 2003\n|ff = [[Harlan's Holiday]] <br /> 1999\n|fm = Leslie's Lady <br /> 1996\n|mf = [[Distorted Humor]] <br /> 1993\n|mm = Gilded Halo <br /> 1996\n|fff = Harlan\n|ffm = Christmas In Aiken\n|fmf = Tricky Creek\n|fmm = Crystal Lady\n|mff = [[Forty Niner (horse)|Forty Niner]]\n|mfm = Danzig's Beauty\n|mmf = [[Gilded Time]]\n|mmm = Careless Halo\n|ffff = [[Storm Cat]]\n|fffm = Country Romance\n|ffmf = [[Affirmed]]\n|ffmm = Dowager\n|fmff = Clever Trick\n|fmfm = Battle Creek Girl\n|fmmf = [[Stop The Music (horse)|Stop the Music]]\n|fmmm = One Last Bird\n|mfff = [[Mr. Prospector]]\n|mffm = File\n|mfmf = [[Danzig (horse)|Danzig]]\n|mfmm = Sweetest Chant\n|mmff = Timeless Moment\n|mmfm = Gilded Lilly\n|mmmf = [[Sunny's Halo]]\n|mmmm = Careless Moment (family: A4<ref>{{cite web|title=Practical Joke Horse Pedigree|url=http://www.pedigreequery.com/practical+joke3|website=www.pedigreequery.com|accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>)\n}}\n\nPractical Joke is inbred 5 x 5 to Halo, meaning Halo appears twice in the fifth generation of Practical Joke's pedigree.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2014 racehorse births]]\n[[Category:Thoroughbred family A4]]\n[[Category:Racehorses bred in Kentucky]]\n[[Category:Racehorses trained in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Jlvsclrk", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBackground:ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Practical_Joke_(horse)"}
{"title_page": "Darrin Camilleri", "text_new": "{{short description|American politician from Michigan|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Darrin Camilleri\n| image = \n| caption = \n| office = Member of the [[Michigan House of Representatives]] from the 23rd district\n| term_start = January 1, 2017\n| term_end = \n| predecessor = [[Pat Somerville]]\n| successor = \n| birth_name = Darrin Quiroz Camilleri\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|1|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Dearborn, Michigan|Dearborn]], [[Michigan]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n| party = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| alma_mater = [[Kalamazoo College]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])}}\n| residence = [[Brownstown, Michigan]]\n}}\n\n'''Darrin Camilleri''' (born January 28, 1992) is an American politician from [[Michigan]] who represents the 23rd District in the [[Michigan House of Representatives]] since 2017.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://housedems.com/camilleri |title=News From Rep. Camilleri |publisher=housedems.com |date= |accessdate=2019-01-17}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|author=Danielle Portteus |url=https://www.monroenews.com/news/20181108/election-recap-camilleri-re-elected-as-michigan-representative |title=Election recap: Camilleri re-elected as Michigan representative |publisher=Monroe News |date=2018-11-08 |accessdate=2019-01-17}}</ref> A member of the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]], his constituency includes several [[Downriver]] communities, including [[Brownstown Charter Township, Michigan|Brownstown]], [[Gibraltar, Michigan|Gibraltar]], [[Grosse Ile Township, Michigan|Grosse Ile]], [[Huron Township, Michigan|Huron]], [[Trenton, Michigan|Trenton]] and [[Woodhaven, Michigan|Woodhaven]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Early life and education ==\nCamilleri was born in [[Dearborn, Michigan]], to a [[Maltese Americans|Maltese-American]] immigrant father and a second-generation [[Mexican Americans|Mexican-American]] mother.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/170332/darrin-camilleri#.XSzsfpNKgUs|title=Darrin Camilleri's Biography|website=VoteSmart|access-date=July 15, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.darrincamilleri.com/meet-darrin|title=Meet Darrin|website=Darrin Camilleri for State Representative|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/why-we-run-young-people-in-government/why-we-run-darrin-camilleri-413e9d487d93|title=Why We Run: Darrin Camilleri \u2013 Why We Run (And You Can, Too!)|last=Something|first=Run for|date=2017-04-12|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> He is the oldest of three children.<ref name=\":3\" /> After graduating from [[Gabriel Richard Catholic High School]] in [[Riverview, Michigan]], he pursued a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science and Government from [[Kalamazoo College]], which he received in 2014.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.crainsdetroit.com/article/20170428/AWARDS20/170429873/darrin-camilleri-25|title=Darrin Camilleri, 25|date=2017-04-28|website=Crain's Detroit Business|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" /> \n\n== Professional life ==\nDuring his undergraduate studies, Camilleri served as student body president and worked as an intern for Congressman [[John Dingell]]; he credits this experience as \"inspir[ing] him to think it was possible to run for an elected office to serve others.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/many-former-john-dingell-staffers-interns-use-job-he-gave/article_1e86b980-3092-11e9-9a21-139355da2cde.html|title=Many former John Dingell staffers, interns use job he gave them to land meaningful careers|last=News-Herald|first=Pat Andrews For The|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> For two years after finishing his bachelor's, Camilleri taught social studies at Consortium College Preparatory High School in southwest [[Detroit]] through [[Teach For America|Teach for America]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> \n\nCamilleri's first political experience came as a member of the Brownstown Parks and Recreation Commission.<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/two-candidates-believe-they-are-best-choice-for-rd-district/article_5694f501-584f-5ebe-96c8-1acbbef96edd.html|title=Two candidates believe they are best choice for 23rd District State Rep.|last=Twitter|first=Jackie Harrison-Martin jackie@heritage com @JackieMartin22 on|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> \n\n=== 2016 election and first State House term ===\nHe then decided to run for the 23rd District of the Michigan House of Representatives seat being vacated by [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] State Representative [[Pat Somerville]] in the [[2016 United States elections|2016 United States Election]]. Camilleri defeated three other Democratic candidates in the August 2016 primary.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlive.com/news/detroit/2016/08/live_primary_election_results_1.html|title=Primary election results in Wayne County|last=AlHajal|first=Khalil|date=2016-08-03|website=mlive.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> \n\nIn the 2016 general election, Camilleri faced Republican Bob Howey.<ref name=\":6\" /> Earning the endorsement of \u2013 among others \u2013 the [[Detroit Free Press]] Editorial Board,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/opinion/editorials/2016/11/03/free-press-2016-endorsements-full-list/92736356/|title=Free Press 2016 Endorsements: The full list|website=Detroit Free Press|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> Camilleri defeated Howey by 323 votes.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlive.com/news/2017/01/meet_michigans_new_representat.html|title=Meet Michigan's new state lawmakers|last=Lawler|first=Emily|date=2017-01-09|website=mlive.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" /> In defeating Howey, Camilleri became the only Democrat in the state of Michigan to take a seat held by a Republican during that election cycle.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nUpon taking his seat in the Michigan State House, Camilleri was chosen by then-Minority Leader [[Sam Singh]] to serve as one of two assistant House Democratic Caucus leaders.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":7\" />\n\n=== 2018 election and second State House term ===\nIn the [[2018 United States elections|2018 election]], Camilleri faced Republican Michael Frazier.<ref name=\":1\" /> He defeated Frazier 23,416 votes to 17,935 votes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/downriver-voters-elect-their-next-batch-of-leaders/article_2060cc68-e3bd-11e8-9aeb-c37827e1745f.html|title=Downriver voters elect their next batch of leaders|last=Twitter|first=Jackie Harrison-Martin jmartin@digitalfirstmedia com @JackieMartin22 on|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn his second term, Camilleri was appointed as House Democratic Whip.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/camilleri-appointed-monday-to-serve-as-house-democratic-whip/article_85414e0c-0d28-11e9-8c4b-b3b31f90bbf6.html|title=Camilleri appointed Monday to serve as House Democratic Whip|last=Twitter|first=Jackie Harrison-Martin jmartin@digitalfirstmedia com @JackieMartin22 on|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> \n\n== Personal life ==\nCamilleri is a Roman Catholic and is a parishioner at St. Joseph Catholic Church in [[Trenton, Michigan]].<ref name=\":3\" /> He has noted his love of bowling, telling progressive candidate recruitment organization [[Run for Something]] that he was an \"all-state bowler\" in high school and that \"bowling is really big in my family.\"<ref name=\":4\" /> \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Michigan House of Representatives}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Camilleri, Darrin}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Michigan House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Michigan Democrats]]\n[[Category:Maltese American]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:Kalamazoo College alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Dearborn, Michigan]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American politician from Michigan|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Darrin Camilleri\n| image = \n| caption = \n| office = Member of the [[Michigan House of Representatives]] from the 23rd district\n| term_start = January 1, 2017\n| term_end = \n| predecessor = [[Pat Somerville]]\n| successor = \n| birth_name = Darrin Quiroz Camilleri\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|1|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Dearborn, Michigan|Dearborn]], [[Michigan]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n| party = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| alma_mater = [[Kalamazoo College]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])}}\n| residence = [[Brownstown, Michigan]]\n}}\n\n'''Darrin Camilleri''' (born January 28, 1992) is an American politician from [[Michigan]] who represents the 23rd District in the [[Michigan House of Representatives]] since 2017.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://housedems.com/camilleri |title=News From Rep. Camilleri |publisher=housedems.com |date= |accessdate=2019-01-17}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|author=Danielle Portteus |url=https://www.monroenews.com/news/20181108/election-recap-camilleri-re-elected-as-michigan-representative |title=Election recap: Camilleri re-elected as Michigan representative |publisher=Monroe News |date=2018-11-08 |accessdate=2019-01-17}}</ref> A member of the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]], his constituency includes several [[Downriver]] communities, including [[Brownstown Charter Township, Michigan|Brownstown]], [[Gibraltar, Michigan|Gibraltar]], [[Grosse Ile Township, Michigan|Grosse Ile]], [[Huron Township, Michigan|Huron]], [[Trenton, Michigan|Trenton]] and [[Woodhaven, Michigan|Woodhaven]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Early life and education ==\nCamilleri was born in [[Dearborn, Michigan]] to a [[Maltese Americans|Maltese-American]] immigrant father and a second-generation [[Mexican Americans|Mexican-American]] mother.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/170332/darrin-camilleri#.XSzsfpNKgUs|title=Darrin Camilleri's Biography|website=VoteSmart|access-date=July 15, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.darrincamilleri.com/meet-darrin|title=Meet Darrin|website=Darrin Camilleri for State Representative|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/why-we-run-young-people-in-government/why-we-run-darrin-camilleri-413e9d487d93|title=Why We Run: Darrin Camilleri - Why We Run (And You Can, Too!)|last=Something|first=Run for|date=2017-04-12|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> He is the oldest of three children.<ref name=\":3\" /> After graduating from [[Gabriel Richard Catholic High School]] in [[Riverview, Michigan]], he pursued a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science and Government from [[Kalamazoo College]], which he received in 2014.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.crainsdetroit.com/article/20170428/AWARDS20/170429873/darrin-camilleri-25|title=Darrin Camilleri, 25|date=2017-04-28|website=Crain's Detroit Business|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" /> \n\n== Professional Life ==\nDuring his undergraduate studies, Camilleri served as student body president and worked as an intern for Congressman [[John Dingell]]; he credits this experience as \"inspir[ing] him to think it was possible to run for an elected office to serve others.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/many-former-john-dingell-staffers-interns-use-job-he-gave/article_1e86b980-3092-11e9-9a21-139355da2cde.html|title=Many former John Dingell staffers, interns use job he gave them to land meaningful careers|last=News-Herald|first=Pat Andrews For The|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> For two years after finishing his bachelor's, Camilleri taught social studies at Consortium College Preparatory High School in southwest [[Detroit]] through [[Teach For America|Teach for America]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> \n\nCamilleri's first political experience came as a member of the Brownstown Parks and Recreation Commission.<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/two-candidates-believe-they-are-best-choice-for-rd-district/article_5694f501-584f-5ebe-96c8-1acbbef96edd.html|title=Two candidates believe they are best choice for 23rd District State Rep.|last=Twitter|first=Jackie Harrison-Martin jackie@heritage com @JackieMartin22 on|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> \n\n=== 2016 Election and First State House Term ===\nHe then decided to run for the 23rd District of the Michigan House of Representatives seat being vacated by [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] State Representative [[Pat Somerville]] in the [[2016 United States elections|2016 United States Election]]. Camilleri defeated three other Democratic candidates in the August 2016 primary.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlive.com/news/detroit/2016/08/live_primary_election_results_1.html|title=Primary election results in Wayne County|last=AlHajal|first=Khalil|date=2016-08-03|website=mlive.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> \n\nIn the 2016 general election, Camilleri faced Republican Bob Howey.<ref name=\":6\" /> Earning the endorsement of \u2013 among others \u2013 the [[Detroit Free Press]] Editorial Board,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.freep.com/story/opinion/editorials/2016/11/03/free-press-2016-endorsements-full-list/92736356/|title=Free Press 2016 Endorsements: The full list|website=Detroit Free Press|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> Camilleri defeated Howey by 323 votes.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlive.com/news/2017/01/meet_michigans_new_representat.html|title=Meet Michigan's new state lawmakers|last=Lawler|first=Emily|date=2017-01-09|website=mlive.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" /> In defeating Howey, Camilleri became the only Democrat in the state of Michigan to take a seat held by a Republican during that election cycle.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nUpon taking his seat in the Michigan State House, Camilleri was chosen by then-Minority Leader [[Sam Singh]] to serve as one of two assistant House Democratic Caucus leaders.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":7\" />\n\n=== 2018 Election and Second State House Term ===\nIn the [[2018 United States elections|2018 election]], Camilleri faced Republican Michael Frazier.<ref name=\":1\" /> He defeated Frazier 23,416 votes to 17,935 votes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/downriver-voters-elect-their-next-batch-of-leaders/article_2060cc68-e3bd-11e8-9aeb-c37827e1745f.html|title=Downriver voters elect their next batch of leaders|last=Twitter|first=Jackie Harrison-Martin jmartin@digitalfirstmedia com @JackieMartin22 on|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn his second term, Camilleri was appointed as House Democratic Whip.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsherald.com/news/camilleri-appointed-monday-to-serve-as-house-democratic-whip/article_85414e0c-0d28-11e9-8c4b-b3b31f90bbf6.html|title=Camilleri appointed Monday to serve as House Democratic Whip|last=Twitter|first=Jackie Harrison-Martin jmartin@digitalfirstmedia com @JackieMartin22 on|website=News-Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> \n\n== Personal life ==\nCamilleri is a Roman Catholic and is a parishioner at St. Joseph Catholic Church in [[Trenton, Michigan]].<ref name=\":3\" /> He has noted his love of bowling, telling progressive candidate recruitment organization [[Run for Something]] that he was an \"all-state bowler\" in high school and that \"bowling is really big in my family.\"<ref name=\":4\" /> \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Michigan House of Representatives}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Camilleri, Darrin}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Michigan House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Michigan Democrats]]\n[[Category:Maltese American]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:Kalamazoo College alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Dearborn, Michigan]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "replaced: -  \u2192  \u2013 , Life \u2192 life,Dearborn, Michigan\u2192Dearborn, Michigan,", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darrin_Camilleri"}
